@iemejia @jbonofre 
I tried extending the SparkPipelineOptions by adding the get/setSparkJavaContext() but kept getting PipelineOptions serialization issues that's why I decided to store the Spark Context in the runner and not in the PipelineOptions.
Maybe you have another workaround.

Modulo that one question about maven-archtypes, LGTM for what it is.

I was not involved in the discussions, but I am somewhat surprised we are going so deep in groupId. I looked around on Maven Central, and I did not see this for other similar projects. Hadoop seems to only have org.apache.hadoop [almost everything] and org.apache.hadoop.contrib, spark similar, mongo db similar.

@jbonofre can you clarify the motivation? (or point me at the discussion where consensus was reached?)
